Package: loli
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         python3,
         python3-pyqt6,
         python3-pyqt6.qtsvg,
         python3-psutil
Recommends: python3-qtawesome,
            lxpolkit | policykit-1-gnome | mate-polkit | lxqt-policykit
Description: Localhost Linux web development panel
 Loli is a desktop control panel for managing a local web development
 environment on Linux: Apache/Nginx, PHP-FPM, MariaDB, PostgreSQL, Redis,
 Memcached and MongoDB, plus bundled-on-demand phpMyAdmin, pgweb and Mailpit.
 .
 Privileged actions run via pkexec, so a polkit authentication agent is
 recommended for desktops that do not bundle one (XFCE/LXQt/minimal WMs).
 The qtawesome icon set is optional; without it the UI falls back gracefully.
 Downloadable tools are stored per-user in ~/.local/share/loli.
